==Arabic==
===Alternative spellings===
انا، أَنَا: ’ána (I)
ـني، ـنِي: -nī, -ni (me)
ـي، ـِي، ـيَ: -ī, -i (my)

===Etymology===
{{ARchar|أَنَا}} from Proto-Semitic ''*’anāk-'', ultimately Afro-Asiatic (with cognates in Berber ''nekk'', Egyptian ''ink'', Coptic ''anok'', etc.)

===Pronunciation===
{{IPA|/ʔanaː/ [ʔɛnɛː]}}
/-niː/
/-iː/ (after long vowels /-ja/)

===Pronoun===
{{ARchar|أَنَا}} (’ána)
#[[I]] ''(subject pronoun)''.

{{ARchar|ـنِي}} (-ni)
#[[me]] ''(enclitic object pronoun)''.

{{ARchar|ـِي}} (-i)
#[[my]] ''(enclitic possessive pronoun)''.

